{"TopicId":185043,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Maneuver Mode, 74k Apo sitting on launchpad?","CreatedByName":"khadgarion","CreatedById":135658,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-02T17:10:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"khadgarion","CreatedById":135658,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-02T17:10:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t quite understand how this is supposed to work...\u00A0\u00A0 I click the purple Maneuver Mode button while sitting on the launchpad, and it tells me my apoapsis is 74km while I am sitting on the launchpad.\u00A0 Shortly after liftoff, it skyrockets into the 3Mm range.\u00A0 This is not really at all helpful for launching into a low orbit.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I had to guess, I would say my lack of actual maneuver nodes has something to do with it, but I am not really sure.\u00A0 I was hoping it\u0027d help me with getting into orbit (or at least a good suborbital flight).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat am I doing wrong?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://prntscr.com/nwnsu2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://prntscr.com/nwnsu2\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-02T17:10:49Z\u0022 title=\u002206/02/2019 05:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 2, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by khadgarion\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-02T17:15:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223610501\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185043\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221559495411\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00